Voximal VoiceXML browser


Install:

Unzip and untar the openvxi package by using the command:

# tar xvzf voximal_Vx.x_date-distrib.tar.gz
Go to the directory of the openvxi and type the following command.
# cd voximal_Vx.x_date-distrib
# ./install.sh

 
Features and beneficts:

- Application for Asterisk PBX (app_voximal.so)
- Support VoiceXML V2.1
- Support pluging objects with the VoiceXML tag, SDK with API available
- Video support (prompt, record and stream)
- Fax support (send and receive) (option)
- Text-to-Speech (TTS) with HTTP connector
- Automatic-Speech-Recognition with MRCP/HTTP connector
- Text-to-Video (TTV) with HTTP connector
- Voice-Silent Detection (VSD)


The resources:

- OpenVXI 3.0.1 (http://www.speech.cs.cmu.edu/openvxi/)
- OpenSSL 0.9.8b (http://www.openssl.org/)
- Xerces C/C++ 2.7 (http://xml.apache.org/xerces-c/)
- SpiderMonkey 1.5 (http://www.mozilla.org/js/spidermonkey/)
